Tools that will make the development of your startup easier:

**CSS:**

- [LESS](http://lesscss.org/) - makes CSS easier
- [SASS](http://sass-lang.com/) - makes CSS easier

**JavaScript:**

- [CoffeeScript](http://coffeescript.org/) - complies into JS (much cleaner, less syntax)

**MySQL:**

- [Sequel Pro](http://www.sequelpro.com/) - for Mac with Amazon RDS MySQL servers

**Node.js:**

- [NVM](https://github.com/creationix/nvm) - swap the version of Node.js you are using quickly

**Python:**

- [VirtualEnv](http://pypi.python.org/pypi/virtualenv) - builds out Python environments
- [PythonBrew](https://github.com/utahta/pythonbrew) - swap Python versions quickly
- [PyCharm](http://www.jetbrains.com/pycharm/) - Python IDE (Django, Flask, etc.)

**Ruby on Rails:**

- [RVM](https://rvm.io/) - allows you to swap Ruby versions quickly
- [Locale](http://www.localeapp.com/) - manages Rails translations
- [RubyMine](http://www.jetbrains.com/ruby/) - Ruby IDE (Rails, Sinatra, etc.)